details:
Case 163 is a 27 year-old female Singapore Citizen who has no recent travel history to affected countries and regions. She is warded in an isolation room at NCID. She is linked to Case 142.

She reported onset of symptoms on 8 March. As she had been identified as a contact of Case 142, she was referred by MOH to National Centre for Infectious Diseases (NCID) on 9 March. Subsequent test results confirmed COVID-19 infection on 9 March afternoon.

Prior to hospital admission, she had visited Funan Mall (107 North Bridge Road) and PUB Recreation Club (48 Woodleigh Park). She stays at Redhill Road.
